# Shell scripts must use LF so they run inside Linux containers — a CRLF in the
# shebang line breaks execution ("bad interpreter").
*.sh text eol=lf
docker/entrypoint.sh text eol=lf
docker/install-makemkv.sh text eol=lf
Dockerfile text eol=lf

# Every PR appends an entry under CHANGELOG.md's `## [Unreleased]` block, so with
# 3-4 parallel PRs the first merge gives all the others a conflict whose ONLY
# clashing file is this one. `merge=union` is git's built-in driver that keeps
# BOTH sides of a conflicting hunk (concatenated) instead of emitting conflict
# markers — so concurrent `[Unreleased]` additions auto-combine on rebase/merge
# with no hand resolution. It's a built-in driver (like text/binary), so every
# clone honors it from this committed file alone — no per-clone `git config`.
# Caveats (all cosmetic, caught by the release-PR curation pass): bullet ORDER is
# "upstream then yours", and the rare case where two PRs introduce *different*
# new subsection headers keeps both. Release-note extraction is unaffected — it
# only ever reads finished `## [X.Y.Z]` sections, never `[Unreleased]`.
CHANGELOG.md merge=union
